Yesterday was the best day ever because I was out all night learning how to string glowsticks from Shelby and Kenny. It was great, smacked myself in the head a few times. That was hilarious, have a couple of bruises though other than that I did it. Then later on, when the sun was up, we called Kat and she came around noon. We sat outside more and watched Hardball. It was fun, then we watched Space Jam. I slept during it. It was cool I layed on kat and then I woke up about an hour later and the movie was still on. After we watched Space Jam we decided to go to Kat's house. Me and Kenny rode the bikes we had but Kenny had to drop the bike he was riding off. We stopped by Kenny's house and Kenny's mom told him he couldn't go back out so I headed to Kat's house. Kat and Shelby showed a few minutes later carrying a bag of stuff from 7-Eleven and we went inside. We hung out in Kat's room and I played some SC2 and was on Kat's computer. Kat's parents ordered chinese and I had that for dinner. After me and Shelby had finished eating Kat got her grandmother to give Shelby a ride home and I ended up half asleep, laying on Kat's leg in the truck. When we got back I went into Kat's room and curled up on the floor while she went to finish eating. She came up and woke me up after she finished. Then we walked to Blockbuster and I had the glowsticks with me. Kat made me look slow because she learned the same thing I learned in an hour from Shelby and Kenny in 5 minutes from watching me do it like twice. We rented Boogeyman and Princess Mononoke. We went back to her house and played some Tales of Symphonia before going outside and sitting on the swing. I left her house at about 9:50 and got home at like 10:00...... When I got home I got yelled at. Called Kat at about a 11 and talked to her for alittle bit. Went to sleep and woke back up about 15 hrs later...... And yeah....
At Kat's house right now....... Deciding what the hell we should do...... man we both need lives.... We will prolly go play SC2 or Tales of Symphonia.... Dunno yet....

Your soul is vengeful.
That is the driving feeling you have in your
life right now. Someone fooled/betrayed you
really bad and now you are after them to make
them pay. Your heart and mind has been
blackened by your hate for this person and it's
on the line obsession. You need to let go, but
that is something you just are incapable of
doing. Betrayal is something you don't take
very lightly and you can easily make new
enemies. People often see you as a cold and
harsh person who may be in need of anger
management, but they don't know what you're
going through and can't understand. On the
bright side; you don't give up that easy when
you've decided to do something. Hopefully you
will have your revenge, if it is within reason,
and get your honour and dignity back.

are slipping but you don't care, you are having

Your element is Wind. You are the guy/girl that is
unpredictable. No one knows what you're going
to do next and what you're in the mood for.
Studying is not your thing and you would rather
go to a party than stay home. Life is just for
fun and you need to be free to live according
to you. You waste no time on lies, if you feel
or think one thing you say it even if it hurts.
Of course, people may be quite upset but that
doesn't really bother you. Its not that you
don't care, because you do, but in these
situations it's a waste of time. You live up in
the clouds and are quite a dreamer about life.
People often consider you beautiful, but harsh
and they would think twice before getting to
know you. But once they do, they'll learn that
you are always willing to take yourself and
your friends on adventures. Never will it be a
boring time with you and your friends
appreciate that. You are not often seen sad,
but you have your times. If someone has been
mean to you, you can quite easily trash-talk
them for betraying you. Nevertheless, you are
most of the time a good spirit who just want to
have some fun. Rate and message!
